==English==
===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
French ''[[trompe l'œil]]'', [[deceive]]s the [[eye]], from ''[[tromper]]'', to deceive + ''[[le#French|l(e)]]'', the + ''[[œil]]'', eye

===Noun phrase===
'''[[tromper|trompe]] l'[[oeil]]''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''trompe l'oeils''')

#(''uncountable'') A [[genre]] of [[still life]] [[painting]] that exploits human [[vision]] to create the [[illusion]] that the [[subject]] of the painting is real.
#(''countable'') A painting of this kind.